    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26510.2.12" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Intake Air Heater (IAH) Element</title>
        <figure id="e3001112.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj09/J09038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>IAH element</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The IAH element is a ceramic coiled heating element used to warm incoming air to aid cold engine starting
            and reduce exhaust emissions during warm-up.
        </para>
        <para>The ECM energizes the IAH relay, while monitoring programmed conditions for Engine Oil Temperature (EOT),
            Inlet Air Temperature (IAT), and barometric pressure.
        </para>
        <para>The IAH element is installed in the front bottom center of the intake manifold.</para>
    </svcproc>
